hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider the congruence system over the residue ring $\mathbb{Z}/84\mathbb{Z}$,
$$
\begin{pmatrix}
4 & 5 \\
3 & 4
\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}
x \\
y
\end{pmatrix}
\equiv
\begin{pmatrix}
77 \\
26
\end{pmatrix}
\pmod{84}.
$$
Work from first principles: use the definitions of congruence and the structure of $\mathbb{Z}/n\mathbb{Z}$, and the fact that, for pairwise coprime moduli, solutions modulo $n$ correspond to tuples of solutions modulo its coprime factors by the Chinese Remainder Theorem (CRT). Proceed by reducing the system componentwise modulo $4$, $3$, and $7$ (since $84=4\cdot 3\cdot 7$ with pairwise coprime factors), solve the three induced systems, and then recombine them to obtain the unique solution modulo $84$ guaranteed by the CRT. Express your final answer as the ordered pair $(x,y)$ modulo $84$ written as a single $2$-entry row matrix. No approximation is required; give exact residues.
